place in the same strip mall, but no.\n\nWaited a while, with the employees not freaking about my friend's skull makeup and a male friend wearing short shorts, and were seated.  Not so much available for the vegetarians, and a lot of Thai places will specifically have a menu section for us herbivores, but not here.  Ended up picking yellow curry and some dish with flat noodles and fried tofu.\n\nThe curry was very very mild, and I'd wanted mild, but jeez.  You could've fed that to a baby.  Still good, though.  The noodles were great: tons of tofu, which wasn't in those chewy fried triangles you get so many places, and lots of crunchy fried garlic bits to accentuate everything.  My friends enjoyed their various dishes; one friend generally hates Thai food other than tom yum soup, but she liked that and the other stuff they got (fish, beef-stuffed drumsticks, and gross fried shrimp with their legs still on).\n\nI'd go back, but I wouldn't suggest it, only because my choices were so limited.", "Other than the wait, I thoroughly enjoyed this restaurant. They have my favorite panang curry to date. They also don't joke about spice. I usually order a 7 at most places to compensate for the lack of heat, but the certainly deliver so be cautious.\n\nMake a reservation. Don't be in a hurry. This place is legit. :)", "Probably one of the best thai restaurant in the country.\nINCREDIBLE wine list with a lot of bargains. \nExtensive menu that covers many regions of Thailand. Friendly service. I make sure to go each time I am in Vegas. I love this restaurant", "Some friends are in town for a convention and they ask me to redeem myself by picking a good place to eat for dinner. GOOD they emphasized. (Note: See my previous post about the Bellagio Buffet) Oh, and they wanted someplace off the strip thats not a chain restaurant. Oh boy. Fun!\n\nI log onto Yelp to check out some options. Immediately I see my HUGE A$$ Pancake picture and suggest Hash House A Go Go. Its pretty tasty ther