inated raw prawns with chili paste.. what a great and unique dish. The serving came with 8 large shrimp that I shared with dining companions, but I could have polished off a plate of these.  I also loved the crispy fried duck served with a congac based curry.  Again, another unique dish to me and I couldn't get enough.  We had other dishes that I can't complain about, but these two were clearly the standouts. \n\nOne thing I would mention, the spice level was not nearly as high as I assumed. We ordered \"medium\" and my next go round i would go high as I felt there wasn't much heat at all. That didn't take away from the fact that I really enjoyed my meal here. \n\nPrices are very reasonable for what you get. This is a very good choice to take a break from the flashy casino dining.", "I havent been here in awhile but this is all I have to say.\n\nIt may be a bit off the strip and it may look run down on the outside, but it WILL stuff you with delicious food. Once you walk in, it's like you were transported to a whole new world as the interior is decorated with ethnic influences. And the food is fan-fucking-tastic.\n\nIf you want a breather from the strip and delicious food, come here and murder your diet. It is sin city after all. :)", "I went back for lunch today, What a difference!  I looked at the buffet and passed. Ordered the traditional Thai Beef noodle soup which had tender beef, meat balls, bean sprouts and deep fried pork skin. \n\nThe flavor was perfect just spicy enough to numb your throat and the crunchiness of the fried pork skin was awesome. For dessert I ordered the deep fried banana and the waiter was nice enough to split a full order since I was dinning alone.  OMG!!!! Wrapped in layers of Won Ton skin and inside was ground coconut and drizzled with honey. SOOOO  GOOOD!", "Ive eaten at MANY Thai restaurants, and to me this was a total disappointment. I read the other reviews on here and was eager to try this place out. The portions that they served u